12:05.058 --> 12:07.016
<i>Boy, I like seeing that
for a chop.</i>

12:07.060 --> 12:09.436
You went with
a forged finish on this

12:09.479 --> 12:11.438
with very little grinding.

12:11.481 --> 12:13.606
I like the look of that.

12:13.650 --> 12:16.985
- So I saw you had a lot
of problem with that ring.

12:17.028 --> 12:19.070
It was really fighting you.
- Oh, yeah.

12:19.114 --> 12:23.366
- Just worried about...
That kind of shape is

12:23.410 --> 12:25.535
a little harsh on the hand.

12:25.579 --> 12:27.996
- Bob, please present
your blade to the judges.

12:28.039 --> 12:29.664
<i>¶ ¶</i>

12:29.708 --> 12:31.624
<i>- Considering the challenge,</i>

12:31.668 --> 12:33.835
<i>this was a very smart,
economical way,</i>

12:33.879 --> 12:35.670
<i>to stretch this out,
roll it back around,</i>

12:35.714 --> 12:37.422
<i>make a squirrel tail out of it.</i>

12:37.466 --> 12:40.717
My one concern, though,
you didn't physically connect

12:40.761 --> 12:42.343
<i>the tail to the body.</i>

12:42.387 --> 12:44.429
You have any ideas on that?

12:44.473 --> 12:47.849
- Yes.
- Okay.

12:47.893 --> 12:49.142
Guess he's not gonna
share it with us, though.

12:49.186 --> 12:51.853
- I guess not.

12:51.897 --> 12:53.188
- Good feel;
I saw you test it out

12:53.231 --> 12:54.522
a couple of times.

12:54.566 --> 12:56.816
But I can feel that wiggle
in there.

12:56.860 --> 12:58.735
If you're not gonna share with
us what you're gonna do next,

12:58.779 --> 13:01.196
we're very curious to find out.

13:01.239 --> 13:02.530
- Thank you.

13:02.574 --> 13:03.948
- Ron, you're up next.

13:03.992 --> 13:06.367
<i>[rock music]</i>

13:06.411 --> 13:08.661
<i>- You had a difficult blade
to work with.</i>

13:08.705 --> 13:11.039
<i>It was thick but lean,</i>

13:11.082 --> 13:13.374
so spreading that out,
pulling out what you did,

13:13.418 --> 13:15.919
you did a good job.

13:15.962 --> 13:17.712
- You know, Ron,
for the biggest guy there,

13:17.756 --> 13:19.047
you sure have
the slimmest knife.

13:19.090 --> 13:20.548
[both laugh]

13:20.592 --> 13:22.217
Looking at it from afar,
I couldn't tell

13:22.260 --> 13:24.928
<i>if it was enough meat
to support the chopper.</i>

13:24.971 --> 13:28.139
There is still enough there
to make it feel good.

13:28.183 --> 13:30.809
- Kyle, go ahead and present
your weapon to the judges.

13:30.852 --> 13:33.394
<i>- You've handed us
the most finished knife</i>

13:33.438 --> 13:35.814
<i>of all the knives.</i>

13:35.857 --> 13:39.484
<i>Those cracks in the back are
a really big concern, though.</i>

13:39.528 --> 13:42.111
- That's what I was trying
to relieve with the clay.

13:42.155 --> 13:43.780
- All in all,
it's a really nice shape.

13:43.824 --> 13:45.073
- Thank you.

13:45.116 --> 13:46.574
- Well, Kyle,
you actually started out

13:46.618 --> 13:48.243
with what I think was

13:48.286 --> 13:50.745
<i>the closest to finished piece
on the table,</i>

13:50.789 --> 13:53.414
so that brings up a lot
of difficulty for you,

13:53.458 --> 13:55.083
transforming it
into something else,

13:55.126 --> 13:57.293
and I think you did
a really good job with that.

13:57.337 --> 13:59.254
- Thank you.

13:59.297 --> 14:00.672
- All right, gentlemen,

14:00.715 --> 14:02.215
it's gonna take our judges

14:02.259 --> 14:03.925
a few minutes
to make a decision.

14:03.969 --> 14:05.760
Thank you very much.

14:05.804 --> 14:09.806
<i>¶ ¶</i>

14:09.850 --> 14:12.433
- Oh, man.
- That was rough.

14:12.477 --> 14:14.102
- All right, gentlemen.

14:14.145 --> 14:15.687
Let's go ahead and start
with Tobin's blade.

14:15.730 --> 14:17.105
-<i> Well, I definitely like</i>

14:17.148 --> 14:18.606
<i>the design of Tobin's blade</i>

14:18.650 --> 14:20.525
<i>because of the curve.</i>

14:20.569 --> 14:22.277
<i>The issue over here
is with the ring,</i>

14:22.320 --> 14:23.528
just the way it feels.

14:23.572 --> 14:25.530
You're gonna be chopping down.

14:25.574 --> 14:27.866
That middle finger's gonna be
hitting onto that ring alone.

14:27.909 --> 14:30.326
<i>¶ ¶</i>

14:30.370 --> 14:31.786
- Dave, what do you think?

14:31.830 --> 14:34.289
- I like the design;
it's really aggressive,

14:34.332 --> 14:36.124
that forward hook.

14:36.167 --> 14:38.167
I'm kind of worried about
the handle being so thin.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.794
It's got so much weight
in the front,

14:39.838 --> 14:41.129
nothing in the back.

14:41.172 --> 14:42.922
- Just gonna have to be
very creative

14:42.966 --> 14:44.132
about how I'm gonna fix it up,

14:44.175 --> 14:46.301
but it's gonna get done.

14:46.344 --> 14:50.763
- All right, let's
move on to Bob's blade.

14:50.807 --> 14:52.849
<i>- It's got enough weight
in that blade</i>

14:52.893 --> 14:54.475
<i>that it'll chop pretty well.</i>

14:54.519 --> 14:56.311
<i>But the way the ring's
set up right now,</i>

14:56.354 --> 14:58.980
it's gonna bang the heck
out of your hand.

14:59.024 --> 15:00.732
- Jay?

15:00.775 --> 15:02.525
- He rounded his spine off.

15:02.569 --> 15:04.986
<i>Any kind of corner
is gonna be weaker,</i>

15:05.030 --> 15:08.197
<i>as far as stress,
than a rounded radius.</i>

15:08.241 --> 15:10.074
I think that was
a very smart move.

15:10.118 --> 15:11.492
<i>¶ ¶</i>

15:11.536 --> 15:13.536
- I'm not really worried
about anything,

15:13.580 --> 15:14.996
just making it through.

15:15.040 --> 15:16.331
- [chuckles]

15:16.374 --> 15:18.708
- Let's move on to Ron's blade.

15:18.752 --> 15:20.293
<i>- Very, very slim.</i>

15:20.337 --> 15:21.628
<i>How is that gonna affect</i>

15:21.671 --> 15:22.712
<i>the stability of the blade?</i>

15:22.756 --> 15:24.881
The ring, very small.

15:24.925 --> 15:26.925
- They're looking
at my knife right now.

15:26.968 --> 15:30.136
I don't know
what he's doing with it.

15:30.180 --> 15:32.388
- What do you think, Jay?
- It's very lean.

15:32.432 --> 15:36.100
You know, Ron, he had to fight
to get what he did out of this.

15:36.144 --> 15:39.020
- Is there any concern
that this would snap in a test?

15:39.064 --> 15:42.106
- Oh, absolutely.
It's a possibility.

15:42.150 --> 15:45.360
- So our last blade
is Kyle's blade.

15:45.403 --> 15:47.570
- He did start out
with the most complete blade,

15:47.614 --> 15:49.238
which I think was
more of a hindrance.

15:49.282 --> 15:51.074
There was only so much
he could do with it.

15:51.117 --> 15:53.201
I mean, he did alter it
significantly,

15:53.244 --> 15:55.328
which I'm very impressed
by that.

15:55.372 --> 15:58.414
But, again, they were working
with blades that failed.

15:58.458 --> 16:01.459
Don't take any chances.

16:01.503 --> 16:03.127
- Dave?

16:03.171 --> 16:05.213
- I think the design
is beautiful.

16:05.256 --> 16:08.549
<i>But those flaws are still there
from the original blade.</i>

16:08.593 --> 16:11.302
Those cracks were probably
really hard to see,

16:11.346 --> 16:13.388
until he started
cleaning this up.

16:13.431 --> 16:15.390
<i>It wouldn't have been
too late to go back</i>

16:15.433 --> 16:17.225
and grab another piece of steel,

16:17.268 --> 16:20.770
but you get locked in
on what you want to see happen,

16:20.814 --> 16:23.231
and you're just gonna fight
that metal until you get it.

16:23.274 --> 16:24.565
<i>¶ ¶</i>

16:24.609 --> 16:26.234
<i>- Truthfully, I guarantee</i>

16:26.277 --> 16:29.570
you could take it right now,
and it'd not break.

16:29.614 --> 16:31.906
- So, judges, have you
made your final decision?

16:31.950 --> 16:33.449
- Yes.
- Yes.

16:33.493 --> 16:34.493
- Yeah.
- All right.

16:34.536 --> 16:35.618
Let's go tell our smiths.

16:35.662 --> 16:38.579
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

16:38.623 --> 16:44.168
<i>¶ ¶</i>

16:44.212 --> 16:45.795
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

16:45.839 --> 16:47.630
In this first round,
your challenge

16:47.674 --> 16:50.091
was to take a blade
that failed in last season

16:50.135 --> 16:53.302
and turn it into
a success this season.

16:53.346 --> 16:56.097
You all performed admirably.

16:56.141 --> 17:00.268
Unfortunately, one of you must
now turn in your weapon

