17:20.165 --> 17:24.125
Unfortunately, one of you
must now turn in your weapon

17:24.169 --> 17:25.626
and leave the Forge.

17:25.670 --> 17:27.086
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:27.130 --> 17:29.338
The judges have made
their decision.

17:29.382 --> 17:32.383
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:32.427 --> 17:33.384
<i>¶ ¶</i>

17:33.428 --> 17:35.303
Kyle...

17:35.346 --> 17:38.347
your blade did not make the cut.

17:38.391 --> 17:41.976
- Kyle, you were told ahead
of time it was a failed blade.

17:42.020 --> 17:44.645
I would like to have seen you
avoid some of these flaws

17:44.689 --> 17:47.482
that showed up by not just
reshaping with the forge

17:47.525 --> 17:49.942
but reforging the piece itself.

17:49.986 --> 17:51.819
You showed a great
level of skill.

17:51.863 --> 17:54.489
Just... it wasn't enough to pull
out the stops on that spine,

17:54.532 --> 17:56.824
and we just can't have that
kind of structural failure

17:56.868 --> 17:58.659
in the blade and accept it.

17:58.703 --> 18:00.620
<i>¶ ¶</i>

18:00.663 --> 18:03.664
- Kyle, please
surrender your weapon.

18:03.708 --> 18:06.667
<i>[rock music]</i>

18:06.711 --> 18:07.668
- Thank you, sir.

18:07.712 --> 18:08.920
<i>- I'm disappointed</i>

18:08.963 --> 18:11.380
in not making it
to the second round.

18:11.424 --> 18:13.841
<i>I looked forward to being able
to help my fellow veterans</i>

18:13.885 --> 18:16.969
<i>with the prize money,
but I fell a little bit short.</i>

18:17.013 --> 18:21.891
I'm not gonna quit just because
I had a bump in the road here.

18:21.935 --> 18:23.351
<i>Rangers lead the way.</i>

18:23.394 --> 18:25.686
<i>¶ ¶</i>

18:25.730 --> 18:27.021
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

18:27.065 --> 18:28.689
- Gentlemen, congratulations
on making it

18:28.733 --> 18:30.900
through to the second round.

18:30.944 --> 18:33.361
Your next challenge
is to finish your blades

18:33.404 --> 18:36.531
by turning them into
fully functioning weapons.

18:36.574 --> 18:38.407
You'll do this
by crafting handles

18:38.451 --> 18:40.201
and attaching them
to your blades

18:40.245 --> 18:43.454
using the range of materials
available to you.

18:43.498 --> 18:46.415
You will have three hours
to complete this challenge.

18:46.459 --> 18:48.417
You can use that time
to address any flaws

18:48.461 --> 18:50.461
that exist in your blades now,

18:50.505 --> 18:52.839
but use that time wisely.

18:52.882 --> 18:55.716
When time is up,
your blades will be tested

18:55.760 --> 18:59.887
on their strength and
durability in a log chop...

18:59.931 --> 19:01.889
and on their ability
to hold an edge

19:01.933 --> 19:04.225
in a sharpness test.

19:04.269 --> 19:06.060
Remember, at the end
of this challenge,

19:06.104 --> 19:09.063
one of you will be asked
to surrender his weapon

19:09.107 --> 19:10.314
and leave the Forge.

19:10.358 --> 19:11.899
<i>¶ ¶</i>

19:11.943 --> 19:13.276
Good luck, gentlemen.

19:13.319 --> 19:15.486
Your time starts... now.

19:15.530 --> 19:19.157
<i>[rock music]</i>

19:19.200 --> 19:20.825
- First thing I want to do
is try and correct

19:20.869 --> 19:23.411
some of the issues
I have with the handle.

19:23.454 --> 19:25.454
<i>I'm just gonna put slabs
on the side of it.</i>

19:25.498 --> 19:27.165
Just right there.

19:27.208 --> 19:29.542
<i>Probably a synthetic material,
but I may put wood,</i>

19:29.586 --> 19:30.835
<i>depending on what fits.</i>

19:30.879 --> 19:33.254
[humming]

19:33.298 --> 19:35.339
<i>¶ ¶</i>

19:35.383 --> 19:37.133
<i>- Since we've got
to be chopping wood,</i>

19:37.177 --> 19:39.635
<i>I'll pick a handle
with a little bit of grip.</i>

19:39.679 --> 19:42.597
The material I choose is a horn.

19:42.640 --> 19:44.432
I don't know what kind
of animal it is,

19:44.475 --> 19:46.267
<i>but it will be easy
to work with.</i>

19:46.311 --> 19:50.479
<i>¶ ¶</i>

19:50.523 --> 19:52.773
<i>The other guys have a lot
of material on their knife,</i>

19:52.817 --> 19:55.526
<i>so I'm afraid of
the heavy knife that they have,</i>

19:55.570 --> 19:57.653
<i>but I'm just worried
about my own work,</i>

19:57.697 --> 20:00.198
and that's what I'm
concentrating on right now.

20:00.241 --> 20:02.950
I want to win this
for the money.

20:02.994 --> 20:04.535
It's a nice little prize money.

20:04.579 --> 20:06.245
<i>¶ ¶</i>

20:06.289 --> 20:08.289
- I know I have a lot
of grinding I need to get done

20:08.333 --> 20:10.708
<i>to make the blade
as smooth as possible.</i>

20:10.752 --> 20:12.084
<i>¶ ¶</i>

20:12.128 --> 20:13.419
Let's see what happens.

20:13.463 --> 20:15.504
[metal clangs]

