20:18.885 --> 20:20.301
- Just a tad.

20:20.345 --> 20:21.636
<i>I dropped that blade on purpose</i>

20:21.679 --> 20:23.387
because that's how
I test the point

20:23.431 --> 20:24.805
of all the blades I make.

20:24.849 --> 20:26.807
- Honestly, dropping
a knife on its tip,

20:26.851 --> 20:28.643
you'll find out if it's
gonna crack or not.

20:28.686 --> 20:30.186
- It's a good way
to test it, really.

20:30.230 --> 20:32.230
<i>- Across the board,
the tip is usually</i>

20:32.273 --> 20:33.689
<i>the weakest part of the knife,</i>

20:33.733 --> 20:36.692
and if it's gonna chip,
I want it to chip there

20:36.736 --> 20:40.696
<i>so if I have to regrind it,
I can do that.</i>

20:40.740 --> 20:44.325
- You have 90 minutes remaining.

20:44.369 --> 20:45.743
- Oh, the ever-present
clock.

20:45.787 --> 20:47.578
How doth it tick.

20:47.622 --> 20:51.290
<i>[rock music]</i>

20:51.334 --> 20:52.708
- He's got
the angle grinder out.

20:52.752 --> 20:54.502
I'm not sure what he's doing,
though.

20:54.545 --> 20:56.170
- I reach for my angle grinder,

20:56.214 --> 20:58.673
'cause I know that will cut
a trench into the blade.

20:58.716 --> 21:00.508
<i>¶ ¶</i>

21:00.551 --> 21:03.761
<i>And I'll put the pin in
with no problem.</i>

21:03.805 --> 21:06.681
<i>And the blade is thin,
but I realize</i>

21:06.724 --> 21:10.017
this blade is tougher
than I thought it was.

21:10.061 --> 21:15.523
<i>¶ ¶</i>

21:15.566 --> 21:17.024
- [sighs]

21:17.068 --> 21:19.402
I noticed what I thought
was a deep grind mark.

21:19.445 --> 21:20.695
Oh, [bleep].

21:20.738 --> 21:22.113
<i>But I got to looking at it,</i>

21:22.156 --> 21:23.906
and it turned out
to actually be a crack.

