23:49.762 --> 23:52.555
and we're gonna check your blade
to see how well it held up.

23:52.598 --> 23:54.558
Tobin, you ready?
- Oh, I'm ready.

23:54.600 --> 23:55.558
- All right, let's do it.

23:55.601 --> 23:58.519
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

23:58.563 --> 24:00.354
<i>¶ ¶</i>

24:00.398 --> 24:02.898
<i>- I'm nervous and excited
at the same time.</i>

24:02.942 --> 24:05.025
<i>But I'm confident in the blade.</i>

24:05.069 --> 24:06.902
<i>¶ ¶</i>

24:06.946 --> 24:09.864
<i>[rock music]</i>

24:09.907 --> 24:13.367
<i>¶ ¶</i>

24:13.411 --> 24:15.244
[thwack]

24:16.581 --> 24:18.873
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

24:18.916 --> 24:21.584
- Tobin, your edge
held up beautifully.

24:21.627 --> 24:23.878
Right where I was
hitting the log,

24:23.921 --> 24:25.546
it's still razor sharp.

24:25.590 --> 24:28.507
No deformation or wiggle.

24:28.551 --> 24:29.884
Good job.
- [chortles]

24:29.927 --> 24:30.843
Thanks.

24:30.887 --> 24:33.345
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:33.389 --> 24:35.556
<i>- Ron, are you nervous?</i>

24:35.600 --> 24:37.892
- A little bit.
[laughs]

24:37.935 --> 24:39.059
- It's okay.
It'll be over in a minute.

24:39.103 --> 24:40.561
- [laughs]

24:40.605 --> 24:42.563
I'm a little shaky right now.

24:42.607 --> 24:45.399
The knife, it's a little bit
thinner than I anticipated.

24:45.443 --> 24:48.903
<i>I just hope my blade
doesn't shatter.</i>

24:48.946 --> 24:49.946
<i>¶ ¶</i>

24:49.989 --> 24:52.907
<i>[rock music]</i>

24:52.950 --> 24:56.660
<i>¶ ¶</i>

24:56.704 --> 24:58.913
[thwack]

24:58.956 --> 25:01.916
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

25:01.959 --> 25:08.589
<i>¶ ¶</i>

25:08.633 --> 25:10.090
- Well, Ron, your blade held up.

25:10.134 --> 25:11.509
- [exhales]

25:11.552 --> 25:13.093
- For the first few strikes,

25:13.137 --> 25:14.929
it almost felt like
I was bouncing off.

25:14.972 --> 25:16.263
- Mm-hmm.

25:16.307 --> 25:18.349
- But the area that
I was using was sharp.

25:18.392 --> 25:21.143
And it did cut.
Good job.

25:21.187 --> 25:22.144
- Thank you.

25:22.188 --> 25:25.105
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:25.149 --> 25:26.941
<i>- Bob, you're up next.
You ready?</i>

25:26.984 --> 25:28.400
- Might as well be.

25:28.444 --> 25:29.610
<i>Not to sound pompous,</i>

25:29.654 --> 25:30.903
<i>but I'm feeling pretty good.</i>

25:30.947 --> 25:32.321
I did everything I can do,

25:32.365 --> 25:34.245
so now it's up to the judges.

25:36.994 --> 25:39.954
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:39.997 --> 25:43.415
<i>¶ ¶</i>

25:43.459 --> 25:44.416
[metal clanging]

25:44.460 --> 25:45.460
[bleep]!

25:53.219 --> 25:55.302
- Bob, you're up next.
You ready?

25:55.346 --> 25:57.304
- Might as well be.

25:57.348 --> 25:59.473
<i>I'm pretty confident about
how the knife will perform.</i>

25:59.517 --> 26:02.476
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

26:02.520 --> 26:04.562
<i>¶ ¶</i>

26:04.605 --> 26:06.188
[metal clanging]

26:06.232 --> 26:07.481
[bleep]!

26:07.525 --> 26:12.361
<i>¶ ¶</i>

26:12.405 --> 26:13.988
- Well, Bob, we had a problem.

26:14.031 --> 26:15.447
- Yeah.

26:15.491 --> 26:18.659
- We did notice,
at the end of the challenge,

26:18.703 --> 26:21.245
that you had
some minor cracking,

26:21.289 --> 26:23.497
minor fractures
up here at the top,

26:23.541 --> 26:26.250
so the stress of the strike
produced a failure.

26:26.294 --> 26:28.836
<i>¶ ¶</i>

26:28.879 --> 26:30.879
I have to say it was very
comfortable in the hand, though.

26:30.923 --> 26:32.006
- Well, at least there's that.

26:32.049 --> 26:33.257
- So...

26:33.301 --> 26:36.176
<i>¶ ¶</i>

26:36.220 --> 26:37.845
- Gentlemen, because of
the catastrophic failure

26:37.888 --> 26:39.263
on the log chop,

26:39.307 --> 26:42.182
there's no need
to do a slice test.

26:42.226 --> 26:45.978
Bob, you didn't make the cut.

26:46.022 --> 26:47.813
You must leave the Forge.

26:47.857 --> 26:49.857
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:49.900 --> 26:51.984
- Well, I got sent home.

26:52.028 --> 26:53.861
I'm really disappointed

26:53.904 --> 26:57.031
<i>but not terribly surprised.</i>

26:57.074 --> 27:00.117
A broken blade is
essentially useless, so...

27:00.161 --> 27:03.203
<i>Feel like I was able to show
that I can cover my ass</i>

27:03.247 --> 27:07.708
<i>in a heartbeat but not
necessarily the whole time.</i>

27:07.752 --> 27:09.918
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

27:09.962 --> 27:12.421
- Tobin, Ron, good job.

27:12.465 --> 27:13.547
You made it through
to the final.

27:13.591 --> 27:14.882
- Thank you.

27:14.925 --> 27:16.717
- You are both
one challenge away

27:16.761 --> 27:19.428
from the title
of "Forged in Fire" champion

27:19.472 --> 27:21.055
and a check for $10,000.

27:21.098 --> 27:23.098
<i>¶ ¶</i>

27:23.142 --> 27:25.225
Tobin, how do you feel?

27:25.269 --> 27:27.561
- Eh, a little nauseous
right now, but I'm ready.

27:27.605 --> 27:29.563
[laughter]

27:29.607 --> 27:31.565
- In the first two rounds,
you came here,

27:31.609 --> 27:33.734
and you made a weapon
of your own design.

27:33.778 --> 27:35.402
In the final challenge,

27:35.446 --> 27:38.405
you'll be forging an iconic
weapon from history.

27:38.449 --> 27:39.948
- [chuckles]

27:39.992 --> 27:42.743
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

27:42.787 --> 27:44.244
A cutlass.

27:44.288 --> 27:46.622
- Ooh. [groans]
- [laughing]

27:46.666 --> 27:49.166
Arr, me hearties,
we get to make a cutlass!

27:49.210 --> 27:51.460
I'm very excited about that.

27:51.504 --> 27:53.962
<i>- The cutlass is a short,
broad-bladed saber</i>

27:54.006 --> 27:56.924
<i>developed in Europe
during the 16th century.</i>

27:56.967 --> 27:58.884
<i>Although it was made
as a land weapon,</i>

27:58.928 --> 28:01.929
<i>it was quickly adopted as
the sailor's weapon of choice,</i>

28:01.972 --> 28:04.598
<i>largely because it was strong
enough to hack through ropes,</i>

28:04.642 --> 28:06.433
<i>canvas, and wood,</i>

28:06.477 --> 28:08.352
<i>but also because
it was short enough to use</i>

28:08.396 --> 28:10.312
<i>in close-quarters combat.</i>

28:10.356 --> 28:13.273
<i>This made it popular amongst
navies throughout the world.</i>

28:13.317 --> 28:15.484
<i>The last use of the cutlass
in a boarding action</i>

28:15.528 --> 28:19.905
<i>by the British Royal Navy
was recorded as late as 1941.</i>

28:19.949 --> 28:22.449
<i>Its effectiveness in battle
also made the cutlass favored</i>

28:22.493 --> 28:25.119
<i>amongst pirates, as portrayed
in the film franchise</i>

28:25.162 --> 28:26.954
<i>"The Pirates of the Caribbean."</i>

28:26.997 --> 28:28.122
<i>¶ ¶</i>

28:28.165 --> 28:29.581
The length of the blade

28:29.625 --> 28:32.543
must be between
24 and 28 inches,

28:32.586 --> 28:34.795
no more, no less.

28:34.839 --> 28:38.173
And the blade also
must be curved.

28:38.217 --> 28:40.300
- Tobin, he looked like
he was like,

28:40.344 --> 28:42.469
"Oh, this is my weapon
of choice."

28:42.513 --> 28:45.305
- Oh, yeah.
- [groans]

28:45.349 --> 28:47.975
I'm a little worried about it.

28:48.018 --> 28:50.602
- You will have five days
at your home forge

28:50.646 --> 28:52.146
to complete this challenge.

28:52.189 --> 28:54.440
After those five days,
you will return

28:54.483 --> 28:57.109
and turn your cutlass over
to our judges.

28:57.153 --> 28:59.361
They will put your weapons
through a series

28:59.405 --> 29:01.989
of vigorous and dynamic tests.

29:02.032 --> 29:04.867
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:04.910 --> 29:06.452
When the tests are complete,

29:06.495 --> 29:08.078
they will decide

29:08.122 --> 29:10.164
which of you is the
"Forged in Fire" champion

29:10.207 --> 29:12.416
and the recipient of $10,000.

29:12.460 --> 29:15.043
<i>¶ ¶</i>

29:15.087 --> 29:17.921
Good luck, gentlemen.

29:17.965 --> 29:21.675
<i>[rock music]</i>

29:21.719 --> 29:22.885
<i>- I've made lots of blades</i>

29:22.928 --> 29:25.512
but never a cutlass.

29:25.556 --> 29:29.016
<i>The design plan for my weapon
is to keep it simple,</i>

29:29.059 --> 29:32.352
clean, flowing, balanced,

29:32.396 --> 29:37.691
<i>and to keep it to the same spec
that the judge want.</i>

29:37.735 --> 29:39.735
<i>Taking on this final challenge,</i>

29:39.779 --> 29:42.362
it's gonna be
a little different here.

29:42.406 --> 29:45.532
My home shop
is a little bit rustic.

29:45.576 --> 29:47.409
I'm just gonna go at it.

29:47.453 --> 29:49.578
<i>The first step is getting
the whole material</i>

29:49.622 --> 29:51.622
<i>down to the right size
that I want,</i>

29:51.665 --> 29:53.540
to about a inch.

29:53.584 --> 29:56.543
<i>¶ ¶</i>

29:56.587 --> 29:57.961
Ugh.

29:58.005 --> 30:01.799
This is my power hammer
misbehaving.

30:01.842 --> 30:05.427
<i>I'm using the power hammer,
and the belt keep coming off.</i>

30:05.471 --> 30:07.387
<i>My power hammer
is a little bit rustic.</i>

30:07.431 --> 30:09.598
Yep.

30:09.642 --> 30:13.644
<i>The drive belt is slipping off
every time I turn it on.</i>

30:13.687 --> 30:15.312
If I have to bit this metal
by hand,

30:15.356 --> 30:17.648
it's gonna take me
twice the time.

30:17.691 --> 30:19.024
You can do this, baby.
Come on.

30:19.068 --> 30:20.025
Get me there.

30:20.069 --> 30:23.070
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:23.113 --> 30:25.989
<i>¶ ¶</i>

30:26.033 --> 30:28.116
<i>- I'm finally back home.</i>

30:28.160 --> 30:30.160
<i>I just had a great breakfast.</i>

30:30.204 --> 30:32.079
I'm looking forward
to having fun with this.

30:32.122 --> 30:35.749
<i>What I'm looking at doing
is a blacksmith-style hilt</i>

30:35.793 --> 30:40.921
with a kind of mangy,
used cutlass style.

30:40.965 --> 30:43.799
<i>¶ ¶</i>

30:43.843 --> 30:45.717
What I'm looking
to get done today

30:45.761 --> 30:48.762
<i>is have my blade forged out
to shape.</i>

30:48.806 --> 30:53.559
<i>¶ ¶</i>

30:53.602 --> 30:55.519
[bleep].

30:55.563 --> 30:56.645
Oh.

30:56.689 --> 30:58.438
<i>And I accidentally knock some</i>

30:58.482 --> 31:00.774
of the kiln shelving off
that acts as the door,

31:00.818 --> 31:03.443
<i>so I have to let it
cool down before I try</i>

31:03.487 --> 31:05.654
any major repairs on it.

31:05.698 --> 31:09.116
I have to very gingerly
and carefully

31:09.159 --> 31:11.827
try and set it
back where it belongs,

31:11.871 --> 31:15.289
'cause right now
when it's really hot,

31:15.332 --> 31:16.290
it's fragile.

31:16.333 --> 31:19.293
<i>[tense music]</i>

31:19.336 --> 31:20.294
<i>¶ ¶</i>

31:20.337 --> 31:21.795
Ah.

31:21.839 --> 31:23.463
<i>¶ ¶</i>

31:23.507 --> 31:24.798
-<i> Yesterday I had some problem</i>

31:24.842 --> 31:26.800
<i>with the power hammer at first,</i>

31:26.844 --> 31:31.471
<i>but I was able to get the metal
down to the proper thickness.</i>

31:31.515 --> 31:34.933
Now I'm just gonna concentrate
on finishing the handle.

31:36.478 --> 31:38.687
<i>[rock music]</i>

31:38.731 --> 31:40.981
<i>I want then
to split it into two,</i>

31:41.025 --> 31:43.692
<i>almost like a snake tongue.</i>

31:43.736 --> 31:46.361
I want the line
to be a smooth line.

31:46.405 --> 31:50.824
I always like to make my knife
more organic feeling to it.

31:50.868 --> 31:52.576
Come on.

31:52.620 --> 31:53.660
It's getting cold.

31:53.704 --> 31:55.495
<i>¶ ¶</i>

31:55.539 --> 31:57.456
<i>The metal's so thin right now,</i>

31:57.499 --> 32:01.126
I can't bend it back fast enough
before it cools down.

32:01.170 --> 32:03.462
Hammer, hammer, hammer, hammer.

32:03.505 --> 32:05.923
If I don't keep it hot enough,
it will crack on me.

32:07.801 --> 32:09.009
<i>¶ ¶</i>

32:09.053 --> 32:10.510
<i>- After the forge broke,</i>

32:10.554 --> 32:12.679
<i>I was able to find
some fire bricks,</i>

32:12.723 --> 32:14.723
<i>patch it back together.</i>

32:14.767 --> 32:16.683
I feel invigorated again.

32:16.727 --> 32:18.894
<i>I got my blade ground down.</i>

32:18.938 --> 32:21.521
<i>I got the weight
at a point where I like it.</i>

32:21.565 --> 32:23.857
So I'm gonna be forging
a hand guard

32:23.901 --> 32:26.193
for this particular cutlass.

32:26.236 --> 32:30.364
<i>What I'm doing is a repaired
blacksmith-type handle</i>

32:30.407 --> 32:33.533
<i>that would have been done
in the New World</i>

32:33.577 --> 32:35.202
during Spanish colonialism.

32:35.245 --> 32:39.414
<i>¶ ¶</i>

32:39.458 --> 32:41.249
<i>Nighttime, day four.</i>

32:41.293 --> 32:42.876
<i>I'm working with the handle.</i>

32:42.920 --> 32:45.545
<i>I'm looking at it,
and then I just think,</i>

32:45.589 --> 32:47.714
<i>"Screw it; I got to make
something a little bit bigger,</i>

32:47.758 --> 32:49.549
<i>something more comfortable
with the hand."</i>

32:49.593 --> 32:51.760
I'm a little pressured,
but I can't panic.

32:51.804 --> 32:53.887
<i>[rock music]</i>

32:53.931 --> 32:55.722
<i>- I got to start
my heat treating process.</i>

32:55.766 --> 32:58.767
<i>¶ ¶</i>

32:58.811 --> 32:59.726
Okay, here we go.

32:59.770 --> 33:03.855
<i>¶ ¶</i>

33:03.899 --> 33:07.234
<i>Moment of truth, I'm about
to pull this blade out this oil</i>

33:07.277 --> 33:10.320
and see what we have.

33:10.364 --> 33:12.406
Eh.

33:12.449 --> 33:13.740
I think we good.

33:13.784 --> 33:15.117
<i>[rock music]</i>

33:15.160 --> 33:16.910
<i>Once I start grinding the blade,</i>

33:16.954 --> 33:18.620
<i>it's looking good;
it's coming out.</i>

33:18.664 --> 33:20.789
<i>I think it'll pass
any kind of trashing</i>

33:20.833 --> 33:22.249
<i>they want to put it to.</i>

33:22.292 --> 33:24.918
I made a $10,000 zombie killer.

33:24.962 --> 33:27.754
It feels really good.

33:27.798 --> 33:31.967
I mean, like, it will chop
anything in half.

33:32.011 --> 33:33.260
<i>[percussive music]</i>

33:33.303 --> 33:35.095
<i>- I made a new handle</i>

33:35.139 --> 33:37.014
<i>out of some larger material.</i>

33:37.057 --> 33:39.224
Looks very tough and raw.

33:39.268 --> 33:41.768
And today, day five,
is all the finish work

33:41.812 --> 33:43.937
that still needs to be done

33:43.981 --> 33:45.856
<i>and do a little bit of testing.</i>

33:45.899 --> 33:48.859
<i>[rock music]</i>

33:48.902 --> 33:54.406
<i>¶ ¶</i>

33:56.326 --> 33:58.618
Yep.
We're good to go!

33:58.662 --> 33:59.911
<i>¶ ¶</i>

33:59.955 --> 34:01.621
<i>Any enterprising pirate</i>

34:01.665 --> 34:03.290
<i>is gonna want a better grip.</i>

34:03.333 --> 34:06.918
<i>That's where the hemp
comes into play.</i>

34:06.962 --> 34:09.713
<i>My number one priority
going into this challenge</i>

34:09.757 --> 34:12.007
<i>was to make the blade
battle-ready.</i>

34:12.051 --> 34:13.884
<i>I know it's not
aesthetically pretty,</i>

34:13.927 --> 34:17.637
but it is gonna be
a queen of destruction.

34:17.681 --> 34:19.639
Aw, yeah.

34:19.683 --> 34:22.642
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:22.686 --> 34:27.522
<i>¶ ¶</i>

34:33.697 --> 34:34.988
It will kill.

34:42.081 --> 34:44.998
<i>[adventurous music]</i>

34:45.042 --> 34:46.666
<i>¶ ¶</i>

34:46.710 --> 34:48.502
- Tobin, Ron, welcome back,

34:48.545 --> 34:51.004
and welcome to the marina.

34:51.048 --> 34:53.090
Because both of your weapons
are cutlasses,

34:53.133 --> 34:55.342
instruments commonly
used by sailors,

34:55.385 --> 34:59.346
we thought it was only fitting
to test them on this ship.

34:59.389 --> 35:03.016
I hope that your five days at
your home forge was productive.

35:03.060 --> 35:05.102
Tobin, how did it go?

35:05.145 --> 35:06.520
- Ah, overall,
it went pretty well.

35:06.563 --> 35:10.190
<i>I decided to think espada ancha,</i>

35:10.234 --> 35:12.651
<i>which were Spanish swords
commonly used</i>

35:12.694 --> 35:17.197
<i>by certain pirates with
a blacksmith-style handle.</i>

35:17.241 --> 35:19.366
I call it
The Queen of the Damned.

35:19.409 --> 35:20.784
- Nice.

35:20.828 --> 35:23.036
Ron, how did your time go?

35:23.080 --> 35:24.746
- Tried to go fancy
with the handle.

35:24.790 --> 35:27.290
<i>Tried to make a snake tongue
over the blade.</i>

35:27.334 --> 35:30.210
<i>That was a little challenge,
but overall,</i>

35:30.254 --> 35:31.878
<i>pretty well, I believe.</i>

35:31.922 --> 35:34.172
- Your weapons look fantastic,

35:34.216 --> 35:37.592
but as you know, aesthetic
is secondary to performance

35:37.636 --> 35:39.386
under extreme pressure.

35:39.429 --> 35:41.221
We are now gonna put
both of your weapons

35:41.265 --> 35:43.557
through three different tests.

35:43.600 --> 35:45.600
Up first is the strength test.

35:45.644 --> 35:46.644
Dave?

35:48.647 --> 35:50.814
- Gentlemen, the cutlass
was a weapon

35:50.858 --> 35:53.900
that was specifically designed
for naval combat

35:53.944 --> 35:56.153
but was just
as effective on land.

35:56.196 --> 35:58.280
Now, any pirate
that went raiding

35:58.323 --> 36:00.574
would probably run into
a situation where he needed

36:00.617 --> 36:02.576
to work his way
through a barricade.

36:02.619 --> 36:04.411
So to test the strength
of your weapons,

36:04.454 --> 36:08.248
we're gonna break our way
through these crates.

36:08.292 --> 36:10.625
Tobin, you're up.

36:10.669 --> 36:11.751
- Let's do this!

36:11.795 --> 36:14.963
When I saw the crates,

36:15.007 --> 36:16.923
<i>the only thing
I could think of was,</i>

36:16.967 --> 36:18.633
"Those poor crates."

36:18.677 --> 36:21.595
<i>[rock music]</i>

36:21.638 --> 36:28.185
<i>¶ ¶</i>

36:28.228 --> 36:29.228
Whoo-hoo!

36:33.317 --> 36:36.234
- Well, Tobin, it's got
a lot of weight to it.

36:36.278 --> 36:37.903
It's quite a heavy beast.

36:37.946 --> 36:39.946
I like the blacksmith
guard, nice.

36:39.990 --> 36:42.449
But it's so long that your hand

36:42.492 --> 36:45.452
has a lot of room
to travel in here.

36:45.495 --> 36:48.622
A bit of deformation and
a couple of chips in the blade.

36:48.665 --> 36:50.040
- Okay.

36:50.083 --> 36:51.875
- But, Tobin,
this will definitely

36:51.919 --> 36:53.627
break through a barricade.

36:53.670 --> 36:56.296
Good job.
- Thanks.

36:56.340 --> 36:58.256
- Ron, you're up next.

36:58.300 --> 36:59.633
- Let's do it.

36:59.676 --> 37:00.675
Going to the weapons test,

37:00.719 --> 37:02.510
<i>it's nerve-racking,</i>

37:02.554 --> 37:04.137
<i>but I'm hoping
everything works out.</i>

37:04.181 --> 37:06.973
It should have the weight on it
to do the chopping.

37:07.017 --> 37:09.142
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

37:09.186 --> 37:12.145
<i>[rock music]</i>

37:12.189 --> 37:20.189
<i>¶ ¶</i>

37:23.700 --> 37:27.077
- So, Ron, though
your handle is very crude,

37:27.120 --> 37:29.246
it was actually
pretty comfortable,

37:29.289 --> 37:32.874
and your blade shows
no chipping, no damage.

37:32.918 --> 37:34.501
It's a little on the heavy side,

37:34.544 --> 37:37.170
but it didn't feel like
it was pulling me forward.

37:37.214 --> 37:39.839
I was able to control the tip.

37:39.883 --> 37:42.384
But all in all,

37:42.427 --> 37:46.179
it went through some crates.

37:46.223 --> 37:48.181
- To test the sharpness
of your weapon,

37:48.225 --> 37:52.018
I will take your weapon and cut
through fish and then rope.

37:52.062 --> 37:53.770
Tobin, you're up.
- [chuckles]

37:53.814 --> 37:56.690
Let's do it.
I'm ready.

37:56.733 --> 37:59.693
<i>[rock music]</i>

37:59.736 --> 38:02.862
<i>¶ ¶</i>

38:02.906 --> 38:04.948
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

38:04.992 --> 38:09.077
- Well, Tobin, it's sharp enough
to cut through the fish.

38:09.121 --> 38:11.871
It lacerated through the rope,

38:11.915 --> 38:13.540
but it didn't cut
all the way through.

38:13.583 --> 38:15.208
<i>¶ ¶</i>

38:15.252 --> 38:18.003
- I hear the chunk
of the blade go "whoosh,"

38:18.046 --> 38:19.379
right through the fish,
and then I hear it

38:19.423 --> 38:22.048
<i>hit the ground, plop.</i>

38:22.092 --> 38:25.218
Why did it not cut the rope?

38:25.262 --> 38:27.220
I... it's...

38:27.264 --> 38:30.390
Little bit of disbelief
about that.

38:30.434 --> 38:32.100
- Ron, you're up next.

38:32.144 --> 38:33.560
- Go for it.

38:35.230 --> 38:38.231
<i>[rock music]</i>

38:38.275 --> 38:40.275
<i>¶ ¶</i>

38:41.778 --> 38:44.612
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

38:44.656 --> 38:47.449
- Well, Ron, definitely
lacerated the fish,

38:47.492 --> 38:50.243
but it didn't slice
all the way through.

38:50.287 --> 38:51.703
Your edge really
isn't that sharp

38:51.747 --> 38:54.331
to cut all the way through.

38:54.374 --> 38:56.624
- Ron's blade doesn't
go through the fish,

38:56.668 --> 39:00.628
but it cuts the rope.

39:00.672 --> 39:02.422
Huh.

39:02.466 --> 39:04.466
- Bladesmiths,
this is the kill test.

39:04.509 --> 39:07.302
I will take your cutlass
and deliver offensive strikes

39:07.346 --> 39:09.179
to this ballistic dummy.

39:09.222 --> 39:13.641
Then we can see how much damage
your cutlass will deliver.

39:13.685 --> 39:16.728
Tobin, you're up.
- [chuckles]

39:18.190 --> 39:21.107
<i>[intense music]</i>

39:21.151 --> 39:25.028
<i>¶ ¶</i>

39:29.493 --> 39:33.161
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:33.205 --> 39:35.789
- That cut right
through the chest,

39:35.832 --> 39:40.627
a laceration into the pectoral
muscle right here.

39:40.670 --> 39:44.130
Not much on this
slash here, but...

39:44.174 --> 39:45.131
<i>¶ ¶</i>

39:45.175 --> 39:46.841
Huh.

39:46.885 --> 39:50.136
- [laughs]
- That's all the way through.

39:50.180 --> 39:53.640
It will kill.
- Yeah! [laughs]

39:55.018 --> 39:56.684
- Ron, you're up next.
You ready?

39:56.728 --> 39:58.144
- I'm ready.

39:58.188 --> 40:01.147
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

40:01.191 --> 40:02.899
<i>¶ ¶</i>

40:02.943 --> 40:05.902
<i>[rock music]</i>

40:05.946 --> 40:13.946
<i>¶ ¶</i>

40:14.079 --> 40:16.996
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

40:17.040 --> 40:21.543
<i>¶ ¶</i>

40:21.586 --> 40:26.506
- Ron, there are
no visible marks.

40:26.550 --> 40:30.009
Unfortunately,
your blade will not kill.

40:30.053 --> 40:32.011
<i>¶ ¶</i>

40:32.055 --> 40:35.181
<i>- I'm completely shocked
there's no damage on the dummy.</i>

40:35.225 --> 40:36.850
I'm shocked.

40:36.893 --> 40:38.601
<i>¶ ¶</i>

40:38.645 --> 40:40.186
[bleep].

40:40.230 --> 40:42.689
<i>¶ ¶</i>

40:42.732 --> 40:46.192
- Tobin, Ron, you were both
given five days

40:46.236 --> 40:49.863
at your home forge to create
signature cutlasses

40:49.906 --> 40:53.867
to perform in our final round
of testing.

40:53.910 --> 40:55.243
Doug.

40:55.287 --> 40:57.036
- Ron, the balance of your blade

40:57.080 --> 41:00.039
<i>allowed me to move around
in a fluid motion.</i>

41:00.083 --> 41:02.792
<i>It's got good balance
for recovery as well.</i>

41:02.836 --> 41:05.712
But a cutlass is
a thrust and slash weapon.

41:05.755 --> 41:08.298
In one test, it just
didn't perform that way.

41:08.341 --> 41:09.757
<i>¶ ¶</i>

41:09.801 --> 41:13.052
- Tobin, I love the edge
geometry of your blade.

41:13.096 --> 41:15.722
<i>It's got good flats
and a good, thin taper</i>

41:15.765 --> 41:17.432
<i>that allowed it to cut well,</i>

41:17.476 --> 41:19.196
<i>but I would've liked
to have seen that blade</i>

41:19.227 --> 41:21.561
in height reduced by about 1/3.

41:21.605 --> 41:23.104
I think you would've got
a better heat treat,

41:23.148 --> 41:24.522
and it would've prevented
the chipping

41:24.566 --> 41:27.233
on the edge of your blade.

41:27.277 --> 41:30.570
- Bladesmiths, you've both done
commendable work,

41:30.614 --> 41:33.072
but it's time for one of you
to leave the Forge

41:33.116 --> 41:34.574
and one of you to be declared

41:34.618 --> 41:36.409
the "Forged in Fire" champion.

41:36.453 --> 41:38.536
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

41:38.580 --> 41:39.621
Tobin...

41:39.664 --> 41:40.914
congratulations.

41:40.957 --> 41:42.165
You are the "Forged in Fire"
champion.

41:42.209 --> 41:45.585
<i>[rock music]</i>

41:45.629 --> 41:47.086
- Thank you.

41:47.130 --> 41:48.755
<i>¶ ¶</i>

41:48.798 --> 41:51.633
- Ron, your blade
did not make the cut.

41:51.676 --> 41:53.510
- Ron, we pushed
your blade hard.

41:53.553 --> 41:55.553
It held its edge
through the strength test,

41:55.597 --> 42:00.350
but in the end, a cutlass has
to be a cut and thrust sword,

42:00.393 --> 42:03.645
and in the kill test,
it just didn't perform.

42:03.688 --> 42:05.104
- Please surrender your weapon.

42:05.148 --> 42:07.982
<i>¶ ¶</i>

42:08.026 --> 42:09.108
Thank you, Ron.
- Thank you.

42:09.152 --> 42:10.652
I'm not bitter towards Tobin.

42:10.695 --> 42:11.945
I'm not bitter towards anybody.

42:11.988 --> 42:13.196
<i>I had a great experience.</i>

42:13.240 --> 42:14.948
Yeah.

42:14.991 --> 42:17.784
Lesson that I learned today
is to keep your blade sharp.

42:17.827 --> 42:19.786
<i>¶ ¶</i>

42:19.829 --> 42:22.288
- Tobin, congratulations.

42:22.332 --> 42:24.624
You are the "Forged in Fire"
champion,

42:24.668 --> 42:29.837
and you will be receiving
a check for $10,000.

42:29.881 --> 42:32.799
How do you feel, man?
How do you feel?

42:32.842 --> 42:35.802
- [stammering] There's no words.

42:35.845 --> 42:37.345
Like, ah, nothing's coming out.

42:37.389 --> 42:39.931
Frickin' won!
Yeah!

42:39.975 --> 42:41.474
[laughs]

42:41.518 --> 42:42.892
I'm in shock a little bit.

42:42.936 --> 42:44.496
- I like the overall
look of your blade.

42:44.521 --> 42:46.187
I like the whole dark factor.

42:46.231 --> 42:47.564
I like the sweep to it,

42:47.607 --> 42:49.357
and I really like
the edge geometry on it.

42:49.401 --> 42:51.442
- It's just strange.
It's...

42:51.486 --> 42:53.444
[all laughing]

42:53.488 --> 42:56.030
<i>I never win anything,</i>

42:56.074 --> 42:58.825
<i>and the fact
that I won this, I'm...</i>

42:58.868 --> 43:00.451
<i>¶ ¶</i>

43:00.495 --> 43:01.953
[sighs]
I need a nap.

43:01.997 --> 43:04.998
<i>[rock music]</i>

43:05.041 --> 43:07.667
<i>¶ ¶</i>
